<br>
interesting though i didnt know mala line cancelled out shielding...<br>
<br>
i use char mainly for pvp mainly cause i xteam and since it is a bolt spell and my team mates are running all over it tends to not hit the right target, plus char doesnt get resisted often and i seen it take a full hp lvl 60 pally to the first letter in his name before (tks gruffer) but then again i am sure tash malo and the chanter with me helped a lot as well =)<br>
<br>
in regards to velocity... ONLY 2.5 more yellows to go wewt! i so cant wait for that then it will be unfearable pets /drool  /bye to sks with out ht...<br>
<br>
if you are fighting a really really stoopid melee the best spell by far for them is rage of zomm... sometimes melees wont take a swing at the pet (thats all it takes) and taht pet will just rip the shreds out of them. takes a long time to get out though and you only get one kill, but god damn that pet wastes on things, a mage with out a pet up is as good as gone, but two swings from most high lvl melees will kill the pet so have a back up plan   (levitate and high rocks tks verant) i had a low level sk and a low level war on me and i was laughing so hard at how fast that warrior had to zone i ran straight and agroed a bunch of mobs and had to zone myself.<br>
<br>
and yes the fire pets are a absolute joke =/ only good thing for them are queen raids in chardok and that dragon in skyfire.<br>
<br>
anyways thats just me im out =)<br>
